  • Krippendorffâs Alpha values range from -1 to 1, with 1 representing unanimous agreement between the raters, 0 indicating theyâre guessing randomly, and negative values suggesting the raters are systematically disagreeing. As suggested by Krippendorff, alphas above 0.8 are considered very good agreement, and tentative conclusions can be made with data where Î±â¥0.667
